1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:03,100
(The following content may not be suitable for viewers under 15.)

2
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:05,000
(Viewer discretion is advised.)

3
00:00:08,072 --> 00:00:09,672
(Final Episode 20)

4
00:00:10,994 --> 00:00:12,524
Everything we said was a lie.

5
00:00:15,494 --> 00:00:16,564
Friends...

6
00:00:18,764 --> 00:00:20,194
mean nothing.

7
00:00:20,464 --> 00:00:21,464
I lied.

8
00:00:21,824 --> 00:00:25,594
I want to stop feeling guilty whenever I look at you.

9
00:00:25,924 --> 00:00:28,124
Friends? It means nothing.

10
00:00:28,224 --> 00:00:29,324
Yeo Kyung lied, too.

11
00:00:30,394 --> 00:00:34,524
We both said something we never should've said.

12
00:00:35,217 --> 00:00:37,417
Something we would regret for the rest of our lives.

13
00:00:37,794 --> 00:00:41,964
Tae Ha, you'll meet new friends here.

14
00:00:49,764 --> 00:00:52,564
Friends are never meaningless.

15
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:59,191
It's always shocking...

16
00:01:00,051 --> 00:01:01,121
to face...

17
00:01:01,974 --> 00:01:03,704
the death of a dear friend.

18
00:01:06,121 --> 00:01:07,421
What should we do?

19
00:01:21,421 --> 00:01:22,621
You start feeling grief...

20
00:01:23,021 --> 00:01:24,521
once you recover...

21
00:01:25,621 --> 00:01:27,091
from the shock.

22
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:29,521
Even if...

23
00:01:30,191 --> 00:01:31,651
it wasn't the death of your friend.

24
00:01:45,236 --> 00:01:46,921
(Seven days later)

25
00:02:05,091 --> 00:02:07,391
What do you think you are doing?

26
00:02:07,921 --> 00:02:10,451
You haven't shown up in the kitchen for a week now.

27
00:02:10,921 --> 00:02:13,761
Everything is out of order. Customers are complaining.

28
00:02:13,851 --> 00:02:15,951
If this goes on, we'll soon be closing the restaurant.

29
00:02:16,921 --> 00:02:18,191
Close the restaurant.

30
00:02:19,151 --> 00:02:20,991
It's weird for it to be still open.

31
00:02:21,691 --> 00:02:22,791
What?

32
00:02:23,621 --> 00:02:25,451
Who would want to eat...

33
00:02:26,091 --> 00:02:27,591
noodles that were once cooked by a murderer?

34
00:02:29,151 --> 00:02:33,091
Close the restaurant until people forget about him.

35
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:35,261
That's the right thing to do.

36
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:42,291
I'm sorry that he killed your parents.

37
00:02:43,421 --> 00:02:45,351
The fact that Kim Gil Do is a murderer...

38
00:02:45,521 --> 00:02:47,691
was also a big shock to all of us.

39
00:02:48,451 --> 00:02:52,491
But what does Goongnakwon have to do with anything?

40
00:02:53,391 --> 00:02:55,121
We all worked very hard to get here.

41
00:02:56,591 --> 00:02:58,491
I can't just stand by and watch it go down like this.

42
00:02:58,491 --> 00:03:00,951
It's unacceptable. I won't allow it.

43
00:03:02,391 --> 00:03:03,951
Resign from Master of Noodles.

44
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:07,751
You are the one who messed up Goongnakwon.

45
00:03:09,091 --> 00:03:11,251
You were supposed to protect it,

46
00:03:11,351 --> 00:03:12,991
but you ruined it instead.

47
00:03:13,991 --> 00:03:15,121
Leave right now.

48
00:03:16,621 --> 00:03:17,751
I can't do that.

49
00:03:18,991 --> 00:03:20,521
I have to keep my place.

50
00:03:21,051 --> 00:03:23,591
Kim Gil Do will definitely show up.

51
00:03:24,591 --> 00:03:27,721
Even if someone has to die, that's when it'll end.

52
00:03:27,821 --> 00:03:29,121
Stop it.

53
00:03:29,321 --> 00:03:30,951
My friend died.

54
00:03:32,321 --> 00:03:35,821
Burning with vengeance against Kim Gil Do,

55
00:03:36,391 --> 00:03:38,221
I didn't even care about my friends.

56
00:03:40,391 --> 00:03:41,491
I'm the one...

57
00:03:42,291 --> 00:03:44,591
who led them into this mess.

58
00:03:45,321 --> 00:03:46,321
I'm...

59
00:03:47,721 --> 00:03:49,591
practically the reason why Tae Ha died.

60
00:03:55,621 --> 00:03:56,721
Ms Seol.

61
00:03:57,221 --> 00:03:58,591
Let me give you a word of advice.

62
00:03:59,521 --> 00:04:03,821
You don't want my anger firing towards you.

63
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:07,691
I don't think you'd be able to handle it.

64
00:04:08,191 --> 00:04:09,791
So just sit tight.

65
00:04:10,621 --> 00:04:12,921
At least until Kim Gil Do dies.

66
00:04:14,751 --> 00:04:16,491
Let me give you a word of advice, too.

67
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:22,021
Don't get innocent people involved in your revenge.

68
00:04:27,561 --> 00:04:28,721
From now on,

69
00:04:29,521 --> 00:04:31,791
you're no longer the top head of noodles to me.

70
00:04:32,121 --> 00:04:34,691
I will drag you down from that position,

71
00:04:35,721 --> 00:04:37,251
no matter what it takes.

72
00:04:52,021 --> 00:04:54,121
He thinks he can have everything his way.

73
00:04:54,591 --> 00:04:58,191
How worse will it be when he becomes the noodle master?

74
00:04:59,091 --> 00:05:01,451
Gang Sook, aren't you going to do anything about it?

75
00:05:02,921 --> 00:05:04,521
Are you even listening to me?

76
00:05:05,851 --> 00:05:09,061
My gosh, why are you being so cold-hearted?

77
00:05:09,061 --> 00:05:10,851
His friend just died.

78
00:05:10,951 --> 00:05:13,421
We should give him some time to grieve.

79
00:05:14,191 --> 00:05:17,721
What's your problem? You're acting like a dictator.

80
00:05:18,491 --> 00:05:22,021
What? A dictator? Hey!

81
00:05:22,021 --> 00:05:24,251
What? I didn't say anything wrong.

82
00:05:25,251 --> 00:05:28,121
After getting the shares from Mr Ha,

83
00:05:28,391 --> 00:05:31,251
you're poking around here and there.

84
00:05:31,551 --> 00:05:33,321
Just try to understand others.

85
00:05:33,651 --> 00:05:35,451
I understand the restaurant is important,

86
00:05:35,551 --> 00:05:37,321
but nothing is more important than people.

87
00:05:37,391 --> 00:05:38,521
My goodness.

88
00:05:50,591 --> 00:05:51,851
I guess...

89
00:05:52,051 --> 00:05:53,321
you don't get carsick.

90
00:05:53,521 --> 00:05:55,451
I do, if I have an empty stomach.

91
00:05:56,021 --> 00:05:58,051
Let go of me before I scream.

92
00:05:58,291 --> 00:06:00,391
You're the thief, not me.

93
00:06:02,391 --> 00:06:03,391
Stop it.

94
00:06:05,221 --> 00:06:06,651
Oh, no! Hide.

95
00:06:27,691 --> 00:06:30,491
You smell of sweat, car...

96
00:06:30,951 --> 00:06:33,351
and dumplings.

97
00:06:34,221 --> 00:06:35,891
But when all that combines together,

98
00:06:35,891 --> 00:06:37,351
do you know what it smells like?

99
00:06:39,121 --> 00:06:40,491
It smells like Tae Ha.

100
00:07:06,791 --> 00:07:08,321
What are you doing here?

101
00:07:19,951 --> 00:07:21,151
What are they?

102
00:07:24,051 --> 00:07:25,291
They're Tae Ha's stuff.

103
00:07:31,721 --> 00:07:32,991
I can't believe this.

104
00:07:33,821 --> 00:07:35,791
I keep crying every time I say his name.

105
00:07:37,251 --> 00:07:38,321
Tae Ha...

106
00:07:58,151 --> 00:08:00,821
Don't flatter yourself. I'm just throwing it away.

107
00:08:02,351 --> 00:08:03,451
Please do me a favour.

108
00:08:05,951 --> 00:08:08,691
Please remember my smell.

109
00:08:34,391 --> 00:08:36,791
Mr Park left a big hole in everyone's hearts.

110
00:08:39,521 --> 00:08:41,851
After my father passed away,

111
00:08:43,751 --> 00:08:47,661
I realised how hard it is to miss someone who left me.

112
00:08:49,021 --> 00:08:52,791
You have no choice but to cry as much as you want.

113
00:08:55,121 --> 00:08:58,091
Something has been bothering for a long time.

114
00:09:04,421 --> 00:09:07,991
I once said you have bad blood in you.

115
00:09:10,191 --> 00:09:12,821
I can't believe I had said such a hurtful thing.

116
00:09:13,251 --> 00:09:16,091
It's not like my blood is any cleaner.

117
00:09:17,691 --> 00:09:21,351
What I said to you kept weight me down...

118
00:09:21,661 --> 00:09:23,161
the whole time.

119
00:09:24,091 --> 00:09:26,661
However hard I tried, I couldn't get it out of my head.

120
00:09:29,691 --> 00:09:30,851
I'm sorry.

121
00:09:33,021 --> 00:09:34,921
I really mean it, Da Hae.

122
00:09:38,491 --> 00:09:39,791
It's okay.

123
00:09:41,221 --> 00:09:42,591
I knew that...

124
00:09:44,421 --> 00:09:45,791
you didn't mean it.

125
00:09:53,191 --> 00:09:56,551
Myeong will be going through a tough time.

126
00:09:57,391 --> 00:09:59,421
Ms Seol will make it even worse.

127
00:09:59,721 --> 00:10:02,661
He'll feel like he's being attacked from all sides.

128
00:10:02,661 --> 00:10:04,251
We should protect him.

129
00:10:04,721 --> 00:10:05,821
I know.

130
00:10:07,951 --> 00:10:09,121
Whatever they say,

131
00:10:09,751 --> 00:10:12,551
the person who loves noodles the most...

132
00:10:13,421 --> 00:10:14,661
is Myeong.

133
00:10:17,891 --> 00:10:20,591
I will do what I can to help.

134
00:10:23,891 --> 00:10:26,321
I know very well that you and I...

135
00:10:27,051 --> 00:10:31,051
can't go back to the day we cooked and ate together.

136
00:10:31,691 --> 00:10:32,991
But...

137
00:10:34,661 --> 00:10:36,521
when we're going through a tough time,

138
00:10:37,191 --> 00:10:39,991
we could lend each other a shoulder.

139
00:10:40,621 --> 00:10:41,921
Wouldn't that help?

140
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:44,321
I wish that were possible.

141
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:48,021
I'll do that, Ma'am.

142
00:10:51,091 --> 00:10:52,191
I'd like to...

143
00:10:55,891 --> 00:10:57,021
thank you.

144
00:11:09,091 --> 00:11:11,191
(Park Tae Ha)

145
00:11:17,651 --> 00:11:22,951
(Park Tae Ha)

146
00:11:58,391 --> 00:12:00,891
(So Tae Seop is most likely to represent his party.)

147
00:12:42,291 --> 00:12:43,391
Ms Chae.

148
00:12:43,921 --> 00:12:45,191
Is something wrong?

149
00:13:00,951 --> 00:13:02,051
Ms Chae.

150
00:13:03,221 --> 00:13:04,621
I'm at fault.

151
00:13:14,721 --> 00:13:17,291
Quit putting on a show, you jerk.

152
00:13:23,151 --> 00:13:24,291
Take him.

153
00:13:38,051 --> 00:13:39,151
Any news yet?

154
00:13:39,391 --> 00:13:40,621
He's on his way.

155
00:14:01,091 --> 00:14:02,191
I'm sorry.

156
00:14:02,391 --> 00:14:03,751
I'm disabled, you see.

157
00:14:04,821 --> 00:14:06,421
Can we begin right away?

158
00:14:06,691 --> 00:14:07,791
Of course.

159
00:14:08,351 --> 00:14:10,121
I lived waiting for this day.

160
00:14:11,991 --> 00:14:13,091
Come with me.

161
00:14:28,251 --> 00:14:30,851
Do you remember him? Mr Hwang Sung Rok.

162
00:14:31,021 --> 00:14:33,121
How could I forget him?

163
00:14:35,451 --> 00:14:36,451
You look great.

164
00:14:36,491 --> 00:14:37,791
You lost some weight.

165
00:14:39,221 --> 00:14:41,051
Were you under some stress recently?

166
00:14:41,151 --> 00:14:42,521
Not at all.

167
00:14:44,321 --> 00:14:45,691
I even signed autographs...

168
00:14:46,291 --> 00:14:47,721
while in hiding.

169
00:14:49,921 --> 00:14:51,791
People don't care about me...

170
00:14:52,051 --> 00:14:53,751
as much as I thought they would.

171
00:14:53,991 --> 00:14:56,021
They will now.

172
00:14:59,921 --> 00:15:02,021
We'll start with a case you're both involved in.

173
00:15:02,451 --> 00:15:03,691
Mr Kim Gil Do.

174
00:15:04,521 --> 00:15:06,591
On May 27, 2014,

175
00:15:07,091 --> 00:15:10,451
did you order Mr Hwang's murder under a bridge?

176
00:15:12,021 --> 00:15:13,651
What are you talking about?

177
00:15:15,791 --> 00:15:19,891
Why would he want me dead?

178
00:15:21,651 --> 00:15:22,851
These questions...

179
00:15:23,491 --> 00:15:26,021
are based on the statement you gave us.

180
00:15:26,321 --> 00:15:27,651
There was a mistake.

181
00:15:28,691 --> 00:15:30,221
Or maybe...

182
00:15:30,451 --> 00:15:33,421
I felt threatened during the interview.

183
00:15:34,251 --> 00:15:35,451
To be honest,

184
00:15:35,991 --> 00:15:37,921
I can't really remember if...

185
00:15:38,991 --> 00:15:40,321
I made such a statement.

186
00:15:40,421 --> 00:15:41,921
What are you doing?

187
00:15:42,891 --> 00:15:45,991
Every interview is taped and preserved as evidence.

188
00:15:46,651 --> 00:15:49,921
There was no misunderstanding or threats.

189
00:15:50,091 --> 00:15:52,791
What happens if I change my statement?

190
00:16:04,821 --> 00:16:05,821
It can't be.

191
00:16:06,591 --> 00:16:07,691
Did you two...

192
00:16:27,221 --> 00:16:29,091
My previous statement is invalid.

193
00:16:30,521 --> 00:16:31,791
I want to revise it.

194
00:16:43,221 --> 00:16:45,921
Get Mr Hwang out of here.

195
00:16:57,891 --> 00:16:59,291
Did you bribe a witness...

196
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:02,221
while you were on the run?

197
00:17:03,221 --> 00:17:05,291
Take things in the way they are.

198
00:17:05,591 --> 00:17:06,821
Don't imagine things.

199
00:17:07,051 --> 00:17:08,651
You beast.

200
00:17:09,321 --> 00:17:11,791
I think you're a little emotional.

201
00:17:12,491 --> 00:17:15,121
Let me help you out.

202
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:21,091
Congressman So Tae Seop's domestic helper.

203
00:17:22,021 --> 00:17:23,861
I killed her.

204
00:17:24,491 --> 00:17:25,721
That was me.

205
00:17:26,251 --> 00:17:29,821
But the murder of Ha Jung Tae and his wife.

206
00:17:31,691 --> 00:17:34,551
You only have Choi Soon Seok's statement and no proof.

207
00:17:35,251 --> 00:17:37,751
And unfortunately, the statute of limitations...

208
00:17:38,121 --> 00:17:39,451
for both cases have expired.

209
00:17:40,721 --> 00:17:44,651
Then there's the case about Congressman Choi's cheques.

210
00:17:46,551 --> 00:17:49,091
That's on the CEO of Raymond Company.

211
00:17:49,821 --> 00:17:52,721
His name is Lee Jeong Beom.

212
00:17:54,451 --> 00:17:56,721
You decided not to indict him,

213
00:17:56,821 --> 00:17:58,821
so it has nothing to do with me.

214
00:17:59,321 --> 00:18:01,121
You also said that...

215
00:18:01,221 --> 00:18:04,751
I disappeared for a week during my arrest.

216
00:18:05,821 --> 00:18:07,121
I didn't disappear.

217
00:18:07,891 --> 00:18:12,091
I was in an accident and the shock left me panicked.

218
00:18:13,491 --> 00:18:14,821
I lost my bearings.

219
00:18:15,991 --> 00:18:19,021
What about Tae Ha? You killed him.

220
00:18:19,451 --> 00:18:21,751
You killed him to hide your secrets.

221
00:18:22,491 --> 00:18:23,621
Stop imagining things.

222
00:18:24,821 --> 00:18:26,921
A prosecutor should work with evidence.

223
00:18:27,021 --> 00:18:30,621
All your creative guesswork got you in this mess.

224
00:18:31,391 --> 00:18:32,591
You jerk.

225
00:18:35,151 --> 00:18:36,551
Don't, Ms Chae.

226
00:18:38,821 --> 00:18:40,051
Ms Chae.

227
00:18:41,021 --> 00:18:42,191
Listen carefully.

228
00:18:42,991 --> 00:18:45,521
I didn't kill Tae Ha.

229
00:18:46,121 --> 00:18:48,651
I don't care if you believe me or not.

230
00:18:49,421 --> 00:18:50,951
But that's the truth.

231
00:19:14,721 --> 00:19:15,821
Mr Hwang.

232
00:19:17,451 --> 00:19:18,551
I'm listening.

233
00:19:18,921 --> 00:19:21,591
Can you do me one more thing?

234
00:19:24,051 --> 00:19:26,451
Do you realise that we're in...

235
00:19:27,891 --> 00:19:29,151
the Public Prosecutors' Office?

236
00:19:30,691 --> 00:19:32,251
There's something I need.

237
00:19:32,751 --> 00:19:34,021
It will be hard to get,

238
00:19:34,691 --> 00:19:35,821
but get it for me.

239
00:19:35,991 --> 00:19:37,591
People don't procure things.

240
00:19:38,091 --> 00:19:39,361
Money does.

241
00:19:40,861 --> 00:19:42,651
What is it you need?

242
00:19:46,621 --> 00:19:50,491
Does this mean you let Kim Gil Do off completely,

243
00:19:52,091 --> 00:19:53,791
while making us look like...

244
00:19:53,891 --> 00:19:57,091
we arrest the innocent and coerce statements from them?

245
00:19:57,951 --> 00:20:00,491
- Is that right? - Please give me more time, Sir.

246
00:20:00,721 --> 00:20:02,391
- If I look into... - What then?

247
00:20:03,891 --> 00:20:05,991
Will you find evidence you couldn't before?

248
00:20:06,651 --> 00:20:09,421
In just seven days, he bribed a witness...

249
00:20:09,521 --> 00:20:10,991
and destroyed evidence,

250
00:20:11,091 --> 00:20:12,791
while you sat and did nothing.

251
00:20:15,251 --> 00:20:16,251
I apologise.

252
00:20:16,251 --> 00:20:18,121
I heard you accepted a bribe.

253
00:20:18,451 --> 00:20:20,691
I also know you gave it all to an orphanage.

254
00:20:20,821 --> 00:20:23,551
I understand that you had no choice at the time.

255
00:20:23,651 --> 00:20:24,651
But...

256
00:20:26,021 --> 00:20:27,551
a crime is still a crime.

257
00:20:28,691 --> 00:20:30,821
You can choose 1 of 2 options.

258
00:20:30,921 --> 00:20:32,321
Be dismissed...

259
00:20:32,551 --> 00:20:35,451
or be arrested for accepting a bribe.

260
00:20:41,521 --> 00:20:42,821
Dismiss me.

261
00:20:44,251 --> 00:20:47,821
You're now suspended until you're officially dismissed.

262
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:50,891
You are forbidden from working as a prosecutor.

263
00:20:54,361 --> 00:20:57,221
(Goongnakwon's Kim Gil Do Appears Voluntarily)

264
00:21:04,821 --> 00:21:06,551
This little insect.

265
00:21:06,821 --> 00:21:07,921
Shall I deal with him?

266
00:21:09,721 --> 00:21:11,551
We can't get into trouble...

267
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:15,151
right before an important event.

268
00:21:16,321 --> 00:21:18,891
I will take over the party convention...

269
00:21:19,191 --> 00:21:21,521
and then run for president.

270
00:21:24,551 --> 00:21:26,751
I can kill an insect whenever I want.

271
00:21:26,861 --> 00:21:29,751
Tell me if you change your mind, Sir.

272
00:21:31,251 --> 00:21:32,361
Instead,

273
00:21:33,991 --> 00:21:35,391
hire more bodyguards.

274
00:21:36,091 --> 00:21:37,491
Gil Do...

275
00:21:38,491 --> 00:21:40,051
will come for me.

276
00:21:42,451 --> 00:21:44,891
