00:44:06,091 --> 00:44:08,291
We can talk this out.

556
00:44:09,691 --> 00:44:11,721
You want the gold badge, right? I'll give you one.

557
00:44:11,821 --> 00:44:13,351
I'll give you 10 if that's what you need.

558
00:44:13,491 --> 00:44:15,921
Calm down, Gil Do. Calm down.

559
00:44:16,021 --> 00:44:18,821
This is not right. You've misunderstood something.

560
00:44:19,091 --> 00:44:20,121
Stop it.

561
00:44:23,021 --> 00:44:24,491
I will live as a beast...

562
00:44:25,251 --> 00:44:27,091
for one more day.

563
00:44:29,651 --> 00:44:30,851
Goodbye.

564
00:46:24,051 --> 00:46:25,591
Were you waiting for me?

565
00:46:26,351 --> 00:46:27,621
What are you doing?

566
00:46:28,651 --> 00:46:30,351
Something that a coward like you...

567
00:46:30,951 --> 00:46:32,691
can never do.

568
00:46:49,491 --> 00:46:50,721
Ha Jung Tae.

569
00:46:51,551 --> 00:46:52,621
Park Tae Ha.

570
00:46:54,451 --> 00:46:58,191
You two are dead in a place where I was born.

571
00:47:00,491 --> 00:47:02,391
In my life, there was a time...

572
00:47:03,051 --> 00:47:06,821
when I felt guilty for the first and last time.

573
00:47:08,591 --> 00:47:09,691
It was when...

574
00:47:11,521 --> 00:47:12,751
I pushed...

575
00:47:13,651 --> 00:47:15,851
your father, Ha Jung Tae, off of a cliff.

576
00:47:17,821 --> 00:47:19,891
I've lived by many names,

577
00:47:21,551 --> 00:47:24,691
but I was the happiest when I lived as Ha Jung Tae.

578
00:47:26,851 --> 00:47:27,951
It felt as if...

579
00:47:29,021 --> 00:47:31,121
I was born with that name.

580
00:47:31,651 --> 00:47:33,121
We had to live in agony...

581
00:47:34,191 --> 00:47:36,491
because of that happiness of yours.

582
00:47:40,351 --> 00:47:41,491
I'm sorry,

583
00:47:42,291 --> 00:47:44,021
but I don't feel sorry at all.

584
00:47:45,121 --> 00:47:47,351
All I did was do my best...

585
00:47:48,591 --> 00:47:50,651
to survive.

586
00:47:52,551 --> 00:47:53,621
Is that...

587
00:47:54,491 --> 00:47:55,851
so wrong?

588
00:47:57,591 --> 00:47:59,251
You are a beast.

589
00:48:07,821 --> 00:48:12,221
I thought about mimicking another life again.

590
00:48:13,221 --> 00:48:14,221
But...

591
00:48:15,821 --> 00:48:18,051
I am too tired to do that now.

592
00:48:36,821 --> 00:48:38,151
I stole...

593
00:48:39,491 --> 00:48:41,191
your father's recipe note.

594
00:48:43,291 --> 00:48:44,321
That was...

595
00:48:45,291 --> 00:48:47,221
the beginning of Goongnakwon.

596
00:49:00,991 --> 00:49:02,791
I have one bullet left.

597
00:49:05,351 --> 00:49:06,851
I either shoot you...

598
00:49:07,521 --> 00:49:08,521
or...

599
00:49:09,821 --> 00:49:11,391
myself.

600
00:49:11,521 --> 00:49:12,791
It's either one of the two.

601
00:49:39,721 --> 00:49:41,651
How many people do you think...

602
00:49:42,221 --> 00:49:44,251
get to die in the place they were born?

603
00:49:46,191 --> 00:49:47,751
Is it an unfortunate thing...

604
00:49:48,721 --> 00:49:49,721
or a fortunate thing?

605
00:49:50,021 --> 00:49:51,021
No.

606
00:49:53,951 --> 00:49:55,921
You can't die that easily.

607
00:49:56,551 --> 00:49:57,551
Myeong.

608
00:49:59,121 --> 00:50:00,291
No, Soon Seok.

609
00:50:01,051 --> 00:50:03,251
This isn't you getting your revenge.

610
00:50:04,591 --> 00:50:06,321
It's me putting and end to this myself.

611
00:50:09,621 --> 00:50:11,221
The beginning and ending...

612
00:50:12,621 --> 00:50:14,891
is always judged and decided...

613
00:50:16,521 --> 00:50:17,921
by me.

614
00:50:27,591 --> 00:50:28,691
No!

615
00:50:45,421 --> 00:50:46,421
No.

616
00:50:50,921 --> 00:50:51,921
No.

617
00:50:55,121 --> 00:50:56,121
No.

618
00:51:11,421 --> 00:51:12,521
Hey, Prosecutor Chae.

619
00:51:13,751 --> 00:51:14,751
Take a seat.

620
00:51:15,321 --> 00:51:16,951
You don't have to report your expulsion.

621
00:51:17,451 --> 00:51:18,921
I came to turn myself in.

622
00:51:21,721 --> 00:51:22,721
Turn yourself in?

623
00:51:23,391 --> 00:51:26,121
Are you saying you committed a crime?

624
00:51:29,091 --> 00:51:31,291
On November 10, 2007,

625
00:51:32,291 --> 00:51:34,351
there was a murder case at Sarang Orphanage,

626
00:51:34,991 --> 00:51:36,091
and I'm the murderer.

627
00:51:40,121 --> 00:51:42,921
What? What are you talking about?

628
00:51:43,021 --> 00:51:46,291
I've also committed crimes as a prosecutor.

629
00:51:46,591 --> 00:51:48,921
I destroyed evidence, took bribes, assisted murder...

630
00:51:49,451 --> 00:51:51,091
and did many more.

631
00:52:05,121 --> 00:52:06,691
(Top Head of Noodles, Moo Myeong)

632
00:52:52,521 --> 00:52:54,491
Everyone is leaving.

633
00:52:55,591 --> 00:52:56,821
One after the other.

634
00:53:07,291 --> 00:53:10,491
My father put his entire life into these recipes.

635
00:53:14,991 --> 00:53:16,591
Your father stole it,

636
00:53:17,151 --> 00:53:18,891
but I am giving this to you.

637
00:53:21,951 --> 00:53:23,921
Why are you giving this to me?

638
00:53:24,121 --> 00:53:25,321
Please keep Goongnakwon going.

639
00:53:26,851 --> 00:53:29,691
You're the only one who can make noodles...

640
00:53:31,221 --> 00:53:32,921
with your heart, not just with your hands.

641
00:53:33,621 --> 00:53:34,721
So keep it going.

642
00:53:42,551 --> 00:53:43,951
(Three years later)

643
00:53:57,221 --> 00:53:58,221
Hello.

644
00:54:00,951 --> 00:54:03,351
I am Kim Da Hae, Head of Noodles.

645
00:54:05,421 --> 00:54:06,551
As you know,

646
00:54:07,121 --> 00:54:08,491
there has been many complications...

647
00:54:09,151 --> 00:54:11,651
at Goongnakwon for the last few years.

648
00:54:13,191 --> 00:54:15,251
We haven't fully healed from our scars,

649
00:54:15,991 --> 00:54:17,651
and we still have many problems.

650
00:54:20,991 --> 00:54:21,991
However,

651
00:54:22,621 --> 00:54:24,551
I believe we can overcome this...

652
00:54:25,021 --> 00:54:27,321
if we all work together as one.

653
00:54:28,151 --> 00:54:31,221
I will also do my best.

654
00:54:34,051 --> 00:54:36,421
From now on, everything I say is an order,

655
00:54:36,591 --> 00:54:38,451
not a request.

656
00:54:38,791 --> 00:54:40,621
I will not take any objections,

657
00:54:40,791 --> 00:54:43,321
and I won't tolerate disobedience.

658
00:54:46,351 --> 00:54:48,351
From now on, everything I say is an order,

659
00:54:49,221 --> 00:54:50,921
not a request.

660
00:54:51,221 --> 00:54:53,321
I will not take any objections,

661
00:54:53,491 --> 00:54:56,221
and I won't tolerate disobedience.

662
00:55:00,521 --> 00:55:01,951
Let's begin with two servings of...

663
00:55:02,151 --> 00:55:03,651
royal pheasant buckwheat noodles.

664
00:55:04,451 --> 00:55:05,551
Let us begin.

665
00:55:11,791 --> 00:55:12,921
Why are you so late?

666
00:55:13,221 --> 00:55:16,291
Look at you, putting on make-up and everything.

667
00:55:16,691 --> 00:55:18,621
I wanted to look pretty. Is that bad?

668
00:55:19,621 --> 00:55:20,621
Get in.

669
00:55:24,791 --> 00:55:26,751
What are you doing? Why are you riding in the back?

670
00:55:27,721 --> 00:55:29,221
Am I your driver or what?

671
00:55:30,221 --> 00:55:31,621
You're my manager...

672
00:55:31,721 --> 00:55:33,721
and I'm the next Master of Noodles...

673
00:55:33,821 --> 00:55:36,251
who also has a 50 percent share of Goongnakwon.

674
00:55:36,951 --> 00:55:38,421
I might just fire you.

675
00:55:39,551 --> 00:55:42,551
My goodness, this is unbelievably lousy.

676
00:56:07,591 --> 00:56:09,391
(Park Tae Ha)

677
00:56:14,551 --> 00:56:15,921
I wasn't going to cry.

678
00:56:19,891 --> 00:56:20,891
I...

679
00:56:21,921 --> 00:56:23,491
didn't run away.

680
00:56:25,721 --> 00:56:27,721
I fought everything just like you told me to,

681
00:56:28,891 --> 00:56:30,421
and I'll continue to do so.

682
00:56:32,391 --> 00:56:33,491
So...

683
00:56:35,621 --> 00:56:37,891
please watch over me, Tae Ha.

684
00:56:42,351 --> 00:56:43,351
And...

685
00:56:48,691 --> 00:56:49,791
you too, Mum.

686
00:56:49,791 --> 00:56:51,121
(Kim Seon Joo)

687
00:57:34,921 --> 00:57:35,921
Are you okay?

688
00:57:37,221 --> 00:57:38,221
Look at your hands.

689
00:58:39,491 --> 00:58:40,951
May I have a bowl of noodles?

690
00:58:46,091 --> 00:58:47,821
What kind of noodles would you like?

691
00:58:48,191 --> 00:58:51,021
Shouldn't you look at me when you take my order?

692
00:59:08,451 --> 00:59:09,451
It looks good.

693
00:59:35,521 --> 00:59:36,521
It's good.

694
00:59:41,991 --> 00:59:42,991
So...

695
00:59:44,651 --> 00:59:46,091
we're back.

696
00:59:47,451 --> 00:59:48,491
Both you...

697
00:59:49,251 --> 00:59:50,421
and me.

698
00:59:51,821 --> 00:59:53,251
It took too long.

699
00:59:56,421 --> 00:59:57,551
You're right.

700
01:00:02,391 --> 01:00:03,551
Do you remember...

701
01:00:04,151 --> 01:00:08,221
the noodles the four of us ate at Chimyeon Restaurant?

702
01:00:09,351 --> 01:00:11,051
That was really good.

703
01:00:20,551 --> 01:00:21,621
A bit more.

704
01:00:23,421 --> 01:00:24,521
Just enough of this.

705
01:00:29,791 --> 01:00:30,791
Here.

706
01:00:32,791 --> 01:00:33,851
Some sesame seeds.

707
01:00:34,851 --> 01:00:36,051
- Can I eat? - Yes.

708
01:00:37,751 --> 01:00:38,751
Let's eat.

709
01:00:41,721 --> 01:00:43,751
- Give me that. - He ate too much.

710
01:00:46,421 --> 01:00:47,851
It's really good.

711
01:00:49,421 --> 01:00:50,951
You're eating your hair, too.

712
01:00:53,251 --> 01:00:55,151
- It's good. - Your shirt's dirty.

713
01:00:55,251 --> 01:00:56,451
Thanks for the bow.

714
01:00:57,051 --> 01:00:58,651
- There's more. - Let Yeo Kyung finish it.

715
01:00:58,751 --> 01:01:00,351
- It's mine. - I'll make you more.

716
01:01:06,291 --> 01:01:07,291
Gil Yong.

717
01:01:08,091 --> 01:01:09,121
Will you hit me?

718
01:01:09,921 --> 01:01:10,921
Hey!

719
01:01:11,891 --> 01:01:13,521
Myeong!

720
01:01:14,791 --> 01:01:16,821
- It's mine. - I want more.

721
01:01:20,521 --> 01:01:21,691
- It's good. - It's nice.

722
01:01:21,791 --> 01:01:23,721
- I want more. - I haven't eaten yet.

723
01:01:24,251 --> 01:01:26,251
- Stop it. - Gosh.

724
01:01:26,951 --> 01:01:27,991
Hang on.

725
01:01:32,891 --> 01:01:33,891
Hey.

726
01:01:35,091 --> 01:01:36,151
What?

727
01:01:37,051 --> 01:01:39,091
It's so good.

728
01:01:39,791 --> 01:01:41,491
- What? - Try this.

729
01:01:41,991 --> 01:01:43,091
Eat up.

730
01:01:45,351 --> 01:01:47,221
(Thank you for watching "Master of Revenge".)

731
01:01:47,221 --> 01:01:49,091
Don't they feed you at Goongnakwon?

732
01:01:49,491 --> 01:01:50,651
I guess so.

733
01:01:52,851 --> 01:01:54,891
- How funny. - Come to me if you're hungry.

734
01:01:55,451 --> 01:01:57,391
Okay? I'll buy you a snack.

735
01:01:57,591 --> 01:01:58,621
No thanks.

736
01:02:01,951 --> 01:02:03,321
Yeo Kyung's eating everything.

737
01:02:04,151 --> 01:02:07,321
(Master of Revenge)

